documentation.text: Maps addresses to ETH deposits to be used for paying the submission fee.

addCaller(address).notice: Allow calls from an address on the same chain.

addCaller(uint256,address,address).notice: Allow calls from an address on another chain.

callAllowed(address,address).notice: Return whether the call is allowed or not.

params.courier: The contract that is trying to deliver the message.

callers(uint256,uint256).notice: Maps caller chain IDs to tuples [caller, messenger]. For same-chain calls, the messenger address is 0x0.

deposits(address).notice: Maps addresses to ETH deposits to be used for paying the submission fee.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

sendMessage(address,bytes).notice: Send a message across the L1 <-> L2 boundary.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
